description: Donald Trump's threats against Vladimir Putin are no longer taken seriously in Ukraine, and Volodymyr Zelensky's absence from the August 15 meeting has come as a shock. Many in Kyiv are convinced that Russia will never give up on taking control of the entire country.

headline: Taylor Swift sets October 3 release date for new album 'The Life of a Showgirl'
description: Following her last release, 'The Tortured Poets Department,' which topped charts last year, and massively successful Eras Tour, Taylor Swift has announced the album, as well as its release date, cover art and tracklist.

headline: 'Who can stop masturbating the longest?': The day 'Seinfeld' tackled sexuality
description: 'Breaking the Script' (2/6). In November 1992, the sitcom's popularity soared when, in its fourth season, the four main characters, three men and a woman, made a bet on who could endure sexual abstinence the longest. This direct and funny approach to sexuality opened up new possibilities for television series. Spoiler alert!

headline: The golden age of Paris's techno clubs: 'Your brain switches off, your body follows the rhythm'
description: 'Why Do We Party?' (6/6). Once concentrated in mainstream nightclubs in central and western Paris, techno has spread to the city's industrial northeast, a shift that accelerated after the Covid pandemic.

headline: Jordan's Islamists come under pressure
description: Since the popular Muslim Brotherhood movement was banned, one of its offshoots in Jordan, the Islamic Action Front, the largest party in parliament, has been threatened. The pressure also aims to isolate Hamas.
